Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF) , the New York-
based investment bank that boosted fixed-income trading revenue
in the fiscal first quarter, hired Rohit Bansal as head of
distressed and special situations trading.  Bansal was previously head of distressed debt trading at
 Citigroup Inc. (C) , the third-biggest U.S. bank by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
